What is this?










Investor FAQs
Display all Answers


What exchange does ServiceSource trade on and what is its ticker symbol? 
 
	ServiceSource trades on NASDAQ with SREV as its ticker symbol.

When was ServiceSource incorporated?
 
	We were formed in November 2002 as a limited liability corporation. Just prior to our initial public offering, we incorporated ServiceSource International, Inc. as a Delaware corporation.

When did ServiceSource become a publicly traded company? 
 
	ServiceSource became a publicly traded company on March 24, 2011, with its first day of trading on March 25, 2011.

When is ServiceSource's fiscal year-end? 
 
	Our fiscal year ends December 31st.

Does ServiceSource offer a dividend reinvestment program (DRIP) or other direct means of purchasing its stock? 
 
	ServiceSource does not offer a DRIP program, nor can investors purchase shares directly through ServiceSource. You may purchase common shares through a registered brokerage firm.

Who is your stock transfer agent?
 
	Wells Fargo Shareowner Services
	1110 Centre Pointe Curve, Suite 101
	Mendota Heights, MN 55120-4100
	(800) 468-9716

How can I update my address?
 
	To update your address, please contact your registered broker.

How may I obtain information about ServiceSource's latest financial results? 
 
	Please click on the SEC Filings page on this Web site for all SEC filings.

How do I obtain a copy of your prospectus?
 
	You can find a copy of our prospectus and any other SEC filings in the Financial Information section of this website. 

Who sits on your Board of Directors? 
 
Click here for a list of our Board of Directors.

Who are your auditors? 
 
	PriceWaterhouse Coopers LLP.

I am a ServiceSource employee or a former employee.  Who can I contact about my stock account?
 
	Please click here and contact us directly for assistance.

Do you have another question that hasn't been answered?

